e range of impacts on health: while some may be beneficial, others will be harmful.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Improved understanding of the health impacts of climate change.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>D965160D-5D8F-4F1E-AF7E-E75202A65285</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>56dd9da8761d53.46507331</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Communities and Social Services/Policy,Healthcare</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>http://www.nerc.ac.uk/research/partnerships/lwec/products/report-cards/health/</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>A379615A-417D-46F4-9D5D-B3D0E48A7172</gtr:id><gtr:title>Climate change adaptation in the reorganized UK public health system: a view from local government.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Public health</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/f170457db17430015f3f24512729154b"><gtr:id>f170457db17430015f3f24512729154b</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Negev M</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2016-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0033-3506</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>56cb34b07b9901.06355657</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>63FBC2C0-C7D8-43F1-8D45-045015DB192E</gtr:id><gtr:title>The Lancet Countdown: tracking progress on health and climate change.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Lancet (London, England)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/cb1955a63ae6a39446365f6c06b8776b"><gtr:id>cb1955a63ae6a39446365f6c06b8776b</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Watts N</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2017-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0140-6736</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>5aa91085f31eb6.75763193</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>